<exercise number="95"><statement><p>Show that if the angles of a triangle are <m>A,~B,</m> and <m>C</m> and the opposite sides are respectively <m>a,~b,</m> and <m>c,</m> then
<me>a \csc A = b \csc B = c \csc C</me></p></statement>
<answer><p>\begin{align*}
    \dfrac{a}{\sin A} \amp = \dfrac{b}{\sin B} = \dfrac{c}{\sin C}\\
    a \cdot\dfrac{1}{\sin A} \amp = b \cdot \dfrac{1}{\sin B} = c \cdot \dfrac{1}{\sin C}\\
    a \csc A \amp = b \csc B = c \csc C\\
    \end{align*}</p></answer></exercise>

